March 31, 2026

Type the subject that you would like to explore from the available commands into the 'Type Command + ENTER' space, then type the specific content that you wish to view. For example, you could type 'history,' then 'authority' to read a history essay on authority. 

Type 'back' at any point to return to the main menu. Keyboard users can press the ESC key to do the same. 

Functional on Android and iOS, though specific touch commands (like swiping to go back on an iPhone) are not implemented. If you are having issues typing a command, try pressing/clicking on the 'Type Command + ENTER' space.
